                                         JOHANNESBURG – In the fight against drug abuse, officials from the City of Johannesburg and law enforcement units have seized more than a hundred pipes used by addicts to smoke cyrstal meth. The blitz focused on two suspected drug dens in Turffontein, south of Johannesburg. Spokesman Lucky Sindane says it was a successful operation.“These properties are notorious for being a drug haven and for crime activities in the area.”